```json
{
"application": "GAMS",
"software": [
"GAMS",
"CPLEX"
],
"resources": [
"PBS queuing system",
"scratch space",
"12 core machine with at least 40GB of memory",
"svn"
],
"libraries": [
"gams/23.6.3",
"cplex"
]
}
```

The script runs a GAMS model called "StaticCapPlan" using the CPLEX solver. The script utilizes the PBS queuing system to allocate resources and manage job execution. It uses scratch space for temporary files and requires access to a 12-core machine with at least 40GB of memory. The script also utilizes the SVN version control system to track changes in the "advpower" project repository. 

The script is designed to run a series of GAMS jobs with varying configurations, such as different retirement rates, priority levels, and cheat values. These configurations are specified within the script using various options and parameters. 

The script leverages various GAMS options to control the behavior and output of the solver, including error handling, logging, and output file generation.
